<br>
When I go to RvR, it's to kill. I want blood. I want to do something that's going to mightily inconvenience someone on an enemy team. I want to prevent a keep from being taken, or take a keep myself, or surprise a group of enemies running down the road, or hunt down and take out a sniper. I want to wage WAR.<br>
<br>
What I don't want is to stumble upon a group of Middies schmoozing around with a bunch of Albs or Hibs! One day, one day I will have enough people at my back to do some damage when I come upon such a scene. We will run up and proceed to lay down the thunder on the lamers on the other team, while the lamers on our team get mad and call us names and send me tells saying &quot;Hey, what's your problem man??.&quot; Yes, I will do this. I'm looking forward to it.<br>
<br>
Dueling is lame. I'm here to fight a war, not to farm realm points. <br>
<br>
Agree/disagree? Let's hear it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uakrux.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Akrux</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/30/02 4:28:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling: laudable or lame?</span><hr size=1> Pros on dueling (in no particular order):<br>
1) It helps you understand your skills, your equipment and your enemies weaknesses better.  You can plan a fight in advance and then execute it.  Do this often enough and you are faster during real RvR.  If you lose you can spend the rez effects time analyzing the duel to see what you did wrong.<br>
2) If you are considering starting an alt you can see how it stacks up against your current character.<br>
3) Duels were a part of the wars and intrigues of the King Arthur legend time period.  <br>
4) Farm rps (which skalds do very well in duels).<br>
5) Change of pace from the regular game - personally I am getting tired of pounding on keep doors.<br>
6) There are occasional pauses of peace/truce in any war.<br>
<br>
Cons on dueling:<br>
1) Fraternizing with the enemy.<br>
2) Builds the pathways to xteaming but so do forums and irc.<br>
3) No keeps change hands as a result of a duel.<br>
<br>
Not an exhaustive list to be sure but a start.<br>
<br>
Akrux Adanac<br>
Skald 50 Kay <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/upfalcon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PFalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/30/02 7:13:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=149.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.dallasbest.net/honourbound/images/pf.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling: laudable or lame?</span><hr size=1> Dueling Lame . . .<br>
